* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
* B1700 MIL Test Program 6 — Conditional Execution
* Tests: IF...THEN, IF...GO TO, SKIP WHEN, X/Y comparisons, FL test
* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
*
* Seven sub-tests exercise conditional skip and branch.
* Expected result: T = H000042 (0x42 = 66 decimal, all tests passed)
*
* Test 1: IF X EQL Y THEN  (true → execute GO TO)
* Test 2: IF X NEQ Y THEN  (false → skip GO TO .FAIL)
* Test 3: IF X GTR Y GO TO (false → don't branch to .FAIL)
* Test 4: IF X GTR Y GO TO (true → branch to .T5)
* Test 5: SKIP WHEN X LSS Y (false → don't skip GO TO .T6)
* Test 6: SKIP WHEN FL EQL 0 (true → skip GO TO .FAIL)
* Test 7: SKIP WHEN FL EQL 0 FALSE (FL=0 → false → don't skip GO TO)
*

* ── Test 1: IF X EQL Y THEN (true case) ──────────────────────────────
START       LIT 5 TO X                   * X ← 5 (clobbers T)
            LIT 5 TO Y                   * Y ← 5 (clobbers T) — X = Y
            IF X EQL Y THEN
            GO TO .T2                    * THEN body: should execute
            GO TO .FAIL                  * only if THEN was skipped

* ── Test 2: IF X NEQ Y THEN (false case, X=5, Y=5) ──────────────────
.T2         IF X NEQ Y THEN
            GO TO .FAIL                  * should be skipped (X = Y)

* ── Test 3: IF X GTR Y GO TO (false case, X=5, Y=5) ─────────────────
            IF X GTR Y GO TO .FAIL       * X not > Y → don't branch

* ── Test 4: IF X GTR Y GO TO (true case) ─────────────────────────────
            LIT 10 TO X                  * X ← 10 (clobbers T), Y still 5
            IF X GTR Y GO TO .T5         * X > Y → should branch
            GO TO .FAIL                  * only if branch was skipped

* ── Test 5: SKIP WHEN X LSS Y (false case, X=10, Y=5) ───────────────
.T5         SKIP WHEN X LSS Y            * X not < Y → don't skip
            GO TO .T6                    * should execute (not skipped)
            GO TO .FAIL                  * only if GO TO was skipped

* ── Test 6: SKIP WHEN FL EQL 0 (true case) ───────────────────────────
.T6         CLEAR FL                     * FL ← 0
            SKIP WHEN FL EQL 0           * FL = 0 → skip next
            GO TO .FAIL                  * should be skipped

* ── Test 7: SKIP WHEN FL EQL 0 FALSE (FL=0 → should NOT skip) ────────
            SKIP WHEN FL EQL 0 FALSE     * FL=0, EQL true, FALSE → don't skip
            GO TO .WIN                   * should execute
            GO TO .FAIL                  * only if GO TO was skipped

* ── All tests passed ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.WIN        LIT H42 TO T                 * T ← 0x42 (success marker)
            HALT

* ── Any test failed ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.FAIL       LIT HFF TO T                 * T ← 0xFF (failure marker)
            HALT

